Not fair at all to say that their mana-constrained counterparts can outburst them. That bottom row is burst central. And most of the tops (zac/tryn/gnar/aatrox/kennen/vlad) can build to be pretty damn bursty too. But, with the exception of Lee and Riven, most mana-less champs are weak early game in exchange for being able to stay in lane longer, level to midgame sooner, and then turn the lane around and wreck mid-late game. For the most part, I feel like they require a little higher mechanical skill to compensate for lack of mana management.
